abstract={In the world of human evolution, species with excellent physical and brain abilities do not survive, but only species with attributes that can adapt to the environment at each specific trend can survive. Therefore, in this paper, we propose the future smart city concept and structure, based on mechanism in human evolution. Our proposed platform consists of, 1) “the large archive which consists of many different AI models”, and 2) “various trials and update of AI models”. Then, we deploy these two functions into three hierarchy, i.e. cloud stratum, MEC (Multi-access Edge Computing) stratum and Fog stratum. And these stratums should be nationwide common open platform. Consensus buildings are performed among the tracking and learning of Cloud stratum (wider & long-term in space-time zone), MEC (medium-term in space-time zone) and Fog (narrow & short-term in space-time zone) stratums. At the same time, according to the update of the currently used model, in cloud stratum, various trials are continuously operated in parallel, as background process. New AI models and modules are created, using the gathered historical data, the existing AI models and just finished AI modules. In addition, for this creation of new models, federated learning is carried out through AI, human control/knowledge and the social world. The federation/ensemble/transfer among the followings, bring about another mechanism of Human evolution: a) The large archive which consists of many different models, b) Various trials and update of models, c) Human knowledge/Intervention, and d) Social world (trend, opinion). If the existing models and modules can't cope with the big change, then the new model, which is the federation/ensemble/transfer of AI, human professional knowledge and social under the observed ongoing trend, appear. These federation/ensemble/transfer are effective for not only the adaptation to the new trend, but also the design of future smart city.},
